  "text": "Last but not the least, for any given order of the differential operator, the number of the canonical coefficients, which are solely determined by the scattering equations, remains the same and appears completely unaware of the factor h 0 . This indicates that, if the degree of h 0 is fixed, there are only (n − 3)! independent differential operators [CITATION_1] Consider the following term in the 4-point amplitude for example. The integral in the string-like theory and the CHY form are respectively",
